<div class=3D"sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content=3D"">
  <p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">Here is the biggest mistake=
 people make when purchasing frames for their photographs:&nbsp;they determ=
ine the size of the frame based on where they want that frame to live in th=
eir home. Sounds pretty logical, right? It is.. until you realize that you =
probably won=E2=80=99t be living in that house forever. People move (every =
7-10 years on average), and they take their stuff with them. Which means th=
at perfectly sized frame will soon have to fill a totally different spot.</=
p><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">So how SHOULD you decide on=
 print/frame sizing? You should think about two things 1. what=E2=80=99s ac=
tually in the photograph, and 2. how big of an impact are you trying to mak=
e?</p>
</div>






















