<div class=3D"sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content=3D"">
  <h3 style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">8"x10=E2=80=9D</h3><p class=3D"" styl=
e=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">This is the smallest framed print I sell. It=E2=
=80=99s perfect for kid=E2=80=99s rooms and bathrooms because those tend to=
 be the smaller spaces in the home. It=E2=80=99s also best for a photograph=
 that features one person only and have a fairly close up shot of their fac=
e. This is NOT the right size for a family portrait on the wall. An 8x10=E2=
=80=9D print is still considered table-top size and it=E2=80=99s really a s=
tarting point when considering a framed portrait. Once again, the only type=
 of photograph I would recommend for this size is a closeup of a single per=
son or child. For everything else, you=E2=80=99ll want to size up.</p>
</div>






















