<div class=3D"sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content=3D"">
  <h3 style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">11"x14=E2=80=9D</h3><p class=3D"" sty=
le=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">This is a very versatile size and you can prob=
ably find a spot for an 11x14=E2=80=9D framed photograph in any room.. It=
=E2=80=99s big enough to showcase siblings or a full-body portrait of a bab=
y, but I would size up for a family, although a family of 3 or 4 might work=
 (as long as the image is close up). The thing to consider is how close som=
eone will stand when they will be looking at this photograph. If the viewer=
 will be closer up, you can display more detail.. but if the print will be =
viewed across the room, you will want to make sure the photograph is simple=
 and uncomplicated.</p>
